                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/1713: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-13T09:00:00+08:00"
                            >May 13, 1933—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 12—11:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>430. Following telegram has been sent to the American Consul General at Nanking:
                        <pb facs="0774" n="672" xml:id="pg_672"/>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“May 12, 2 p.m. Italian Legation reports that March and April
                            installments of Italian portion of Boxer Indemnity have been paid.
                            Please so inform Foreign Office referring to the Legation’s note number
                            590, May 3rd, that Legation learns with surprise that preferential
                            treatment has been accorded to Italian Government and that there has
                            been discrimination against the American Government which was the first
                            government to remit for the benefit of China its portion of the
                            indemnity of 1902 [<hi rend="italic">1901</hi>], Please renew request
                            that payments due the American Government for the months of March and
                            April be paid without further delay in order that enterprises dependent
                            upon these payments may not suffer.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
